Every healthy person at least 18 years old, meeting the eligibility criteria, but can donate blood only once in 56 days, that means six times a year.
14 % of the people offering blood are not accepted on average because they are AIDS carriers or malaria, for example, and if they visited the country where the bathing cold is running, they are excluded for a period of one year.
"With these 3% we can maintain a condition that meets the needs of hospitals.
