But to convince people to give blood is difficult, especially to keep and encourage them to become regular donors.
Life is so unsatisfied today that we can only find an hour to give our blood," Francine Décary said.
With an annual budget of $297 million, Hema-Québec supplies not only blood products, but also human tissue, such as bone transplants, heart palate, eye bubbles and skin, which is used almost exclusively for large burns.
