The apocalyptic cord, previously considered biomedical waste, pours blood rich into stem cells that can be used to treat serious diseases, such as leukemia.
"A few weeks ago, we celebrated the deposit of our thousands of blood sample from the bees to the bank and we assume that we will take them over a thousand years.
